{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Key Takeaways","type":"heading","anchor":"Key-Takeaways","level":1},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3 new metrics added: CPU instructions, scroll hitches, app exit reasons"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Diagnostics functionality provides actionable information targeted to specific events"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Recap: How MetricKit Works Today","type":"heading","anchor":"Recap-How-MetricKit-Works-Today","level":1},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"MetricKit is a tool that provides diagnostics and performance data from users’ devices during beta testing and after release - not during development. This data helps you identify trends and patterns in performance regressions.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Three easy steps to start using MetricKit","type":"heading","anchor":"Three-easy-steps-to-start-using-MetricKit","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Link MetricKit"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Instantiate MXMetricManager","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Implement MXMetricManagerSubscriber delegate protocol"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import MetricKit","","class MySubscriber: NSObject, MXMetricManagerSubscriber {","    ","    var metricManager: MXMetricManager?","    ","    override init() {","        super.init()","        metricManager = MXMetricManager.shared","        metricManager?.add(self)","    }","    ","    override deinit() {","        \/\/ Apple recommends to remove a subscriber on deinit","        metricManager?.remove(self)","    }","    ","    \/\/ this allows you to receive metric payloads","    func didReceive(_ payload: [MXMetricPayload]) {","        for metricPayload in payload {","            \/\/ Do something with metricPayload.","        }","    }","    ","}"]},{"text":"How the system aggregates and delivers payloads?","type":"heading","anchor":"How-the-system-aggregates-and-delivers-payloads","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC20-10081-metrics-payloads.jpeg"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Data is collected "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"passively","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" over a 24‑hour period while the app is running."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"At the end of the day, the system aggregates the data into a 24‑hour anonymized payload represented as an MXMetricPayload object.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Understanding Metric Payloads","type":"heading","anchor":"Understanding-Metric-Payloads","level":1},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A payload splits performance data into three aggregation types:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"cumulative","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"average","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"bucketed performance data","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After processing, this data becomes very useful for identifying regressions between builds."}]},{"text":"Limitations of Existing Metrics","type":"heading","anchor":"Limitations-of-Existing-Metrics","level":1},{"numberOfColumns":3,"type":"row","columns":[{"size":2,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A high number of app launches compared to app resumes may indicate an issue, but existing metrics don’t explain why."}]}]},{"size":1,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC20-10081-launch-time-example.jpeg","type":"image"}]}]}]},{"numberOfColumns":3,"type":"row","columns":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Overall CPU time of 78 seconds vs. 739 seconds of foreground time looks good, but it’s unclear whether this is a regression or an improvement because CPU time depends on hardware frequency.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"size":2},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC20-10081-cpu-time-example.jpeg","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"size":1}]},{"numberOfColumns":3,"type":"row","columns":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This looks alarming, but there’s no way to investigate the cause.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"size":2},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC20-10081-hang-example.jpeg"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"size":1}]},{"text":"What’s New in MetricKit 2.0","type":"heading","anchor":"Whats-New-in-MetricKit-20","level":1},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"New metrics added:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"CPU Instructions"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Scroll hitches"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"App exit reasons"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"CPU Instructions Metric","type":"heading","anchor":"CPU-Instructions-Metric","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Added to MXCPUMetric","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tracks daily total retired instructions"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A hardware‑ and frequency‑independent metric"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Represents the total workload of your app","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Scroll Hitch Metrics","type":"heading","anchor":"Scroll-Hitch-Metrics","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"New metric"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A scroll hitch occurs when a rendered frame misses its expected display time during scrolling","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Measures user‑perceivable animation delays","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Provides a time ratio for UIScrollView scrolling: hitching time vs. scrolling time"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"See ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10077-Eliminate-animation-hitches-with-XCTest","type":"reference"},{"text":" for more technical details about hitches","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Application Exit Metrics","type":"heading","anchor":"Application-Exit-Metrics","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Summaries of exit reasons and counts, for both foreground and background"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Useful for diagnosing launch issues or problems with background runtime frameworks","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For a deep dive, watch "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10078-Why-is-my-app-getting-killed"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Introduction to MetricKit Diagnostics","type":"heading","anchor":"Introduction-to-MetricKit-Diagnostics","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlike metrics, diagnostics are tied to specific events"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Contain actionable, targeted information","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To start receiving diagnostics, implement this additional method of MXMetricManagerSubscriber:","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["func didReceive(_ payload: [MXDiagnosticPayload]) {","    for diagnosticPayload in payload {","        \/\/ Consume diagnosticPayload.","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC20-10081-metrics-and-diagnostics-payload.jpeg","type":"image"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you see a regression in a metric payload, you can correlate it with its diagnostic payload"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"MetricKit 2.0 API","type":"heading","anchor":"MetricKit-20-API","level":1},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Diagnostic classes mirror metric classes, with MXCallStackTree introduced"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"MXDiagnostic","type":"heading","anchor":"MXDiagnostic","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Metadata at regression time"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Diagnostic‑specific data (unique to each subclass)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Every diagnostic includes an MXCallStackTree"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Call Stack Trees","type":"heading","anchor":"Call-Stack-Trees","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC20-10081-callstack-example.jpeg"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Backtrace captured when the regression occurred","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unsymbolicated - must be symbolicated off‑device using tools like atos"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Similar structures are used in other Apple performance tools. See "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10057-Identify-trends-with-the-Power-and-Performance-API"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"MXDiagnostic Subclasses","type":"heading","anchor":"MXDiagnostic-Subclasses","level":2},{"text":"MXHangDiagnostic","type":"heading","anchor":"MXHangDiagnostic","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A hang is long‑lasting app unresponsiveness (e.g., a blocked main thread).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Provided data:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"time spent hanging","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"main‑thread backtrace"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"MXCPUExceptionDiagnostic","type":"heading","anchor":"MXCPUExceptionDiagnostic","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(Displayed as “energy logs” in Xcode Organizer)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Provided data:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"CPU time consumed","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"total sampled time"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"backtraces of CPU‑spinning threads"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"MXDiskWriteExceptionDiagnostic","type":"heading","anchor":"MXDiskWriteExceptionDiagnostic","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Provided data:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"total writes caused"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"backtrace of threads causing writes","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"generated when the app exceeds the 1 GB daily disk‑write threshold"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"MXCrashDiagnostic","type":"heading","anchor":"MXCrashDiagnostic","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Provided data:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"exception type, code and signal"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"termination reason"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"virtual memory region details for bad‑access crashes"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"backtrace of the crashed thread"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Written By","type":"heading","anchor":"Written-By","level":2},{"numberOfColumns":5,"type":"row","columns":[{"size":1,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"ismehimeh","type":"image"}]}]},{"size":4,"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Sergei Vasilenko","level":3,"anchor":"Sergei-Vasilenko"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"overridingTitle":"Contributed Notes","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/ismehimeh","isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Contributed Notes","type":"text"}],"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"|","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/ismehimeh","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"|","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}]}]},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Missing anything? Corrections? "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","isActive":true}]},{"text":"Related Sessions","type":"heading","anchor":"Related-Sessions","level":2},{"items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10087-Diagnose-Power-and-Performance-regressions-in-your-app","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10181-Ultimate-application-performance-survival-guide","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10203-Triage-TestFlight-crashes-in-Xcode-Organizer","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10258-Understand-and-eliminate-hangs-from-your-app","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10057-Identify-trends-with-the-Power-and-Performance-API","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10076-Diagnose-performance-issues-with-the-Xcode-Organizer","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10077-Eliminate-animation-hitches-with-XCTest"],"type":"links","style":"list"},{"type":"small","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Legal Notice","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"small","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All content copyright © 2012 – 2025 Apple Inc. All rights reserved."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Swift, the Swift logo, Swift Playgrounds, Xcode, Instruments, Cocoa Touch, Touch ID, FaceID, iPhone, iPad, Safari, Apple Vision, Apple Watch, App Store, iPadOS, watchOS, visionOS, tvOS, Mac, and macOS are trademarks of Apple Inc., registered in the U.S. and other countries."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This website is not made by, affiliated with, nor endorsed by Apple."}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10081-whats-new-in-metrickit"]}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2020\/10081","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (13 min)"}},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20"]]},"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Quickly detect power and performance regressions and troubleshoot app issues when you adopt MetricKit. Discover the latest trackable metrics for your app, including CPU instructions, animation hitches, and exit reasons. And learn about diagnostics in MetricKit that can help you troubleshoot hangs, crashes, and disk writes."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10081-Whats-new-in-MetricKit"},"metadata":{"title":"What’s new in MetricKit","roleHeading":"WWDC20","role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"references":{"WWDC20-10081-metrics-and-diagnostics-payload.jpeg":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10081-metrics-and-diagnostics-payload.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDC20-10081-metrics-and-diagnostics-payload.jpeg","alt":null,"type":"image"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC21-10181-Ultimate-application-performance-survival-guide":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc21-10181-ultimate-application-performance-survival-guide","title":"Ultimate application performance survival guide","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10181-Ultimate-application-performance-survival-guide","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Performance optimization can seem like a daunting task — with many metrics to track and tools to use. Fear not: Our survival guide to app performance is here to help you understand tooling, metrics, and paradigms that can help smooth your development process and contribute to a great experience for people using your app.","type":"text"}]},"https://github.com/ismehimeh":{"titleInlineContent":[{"text":"GitHub","type":"text"}],"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/ismehimeh","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/ismehimeh","title":"GitHub"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10078-Why-is-my-app-getting-killed":{"abstract":[{"text":"Put on your detective’s hat: It’s time to track down those unruly app terminations. We’ll outline the six major reasons apps terminate in the background, and show you how you can use MetricKit to to help you identify key statistics to drive down the rate of terminations. Learn how to prevent problems and recover gracefully from inevitable jetsams, identify any underlying issues, and take actionable measures to fix them. And discover the importance of implementing state restoration to make terminations less jarring — especially where text entry or playback is concerned.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10078-Why-is-my-app-getting-killed","title":"Why is my app getting killed?","type":"topic","kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10078-why-is-my-app-getting-killed"},"ismehimeh":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/ismehimeh.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"ismehimeh","alt":"Profile image of Sergei Vasilenko","type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10076-Diagnose-performance-issues-with-the-Xcode-Organizer":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10076-diagnose-performance-issues-with-the-xcode-organizer","kind":"article","title":"Diagnose performance issues with the Xcode Organizer","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10076-Diagnose-performance-issues-with-the-Xcode-Organizer","abstract":[{"text":"Analyze aggregated power and performance data from multiple versions of your app with just a few clicks. We’ll introduce you to the latest version of the Xcode Organizer and its interactive interface, where you can easily compare and contrast app metrics across releases. Explore disk write diagnostics and scroll hitch metrics, and learn how you can use these to offer better performance, reduce battery consumption, and improve device health for people using your app.","type":"text"}],"role":"sampleCode"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20","type":"topic","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","images":[{"identifier":"WWDC20-Icon.png","type":"icon"},{"identifier":"WWDC20.jpeg","type":"card"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Xcode 12, Swift 5.3, iOS 14, macOS 11 (Big Sur), tvOS 14, watchOS 7.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"New APIs: ","type":"text"},{"code":"WidgetKit","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"StoreKit Testing","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and more.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20","title":"WWDC20"},"WWDC20-10081-cpu-time-example.jpeg":{"identifier":"WWDC20-10081-cpu-time-example.jpeg","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10081-cpu-time-example.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"type":"topic","title":"WWDC Notes","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","abstract":[{"text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","role":"collection","images":[{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"icon"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/ismehimeh":{"images":[{"identifier":"ismehimeh.jpeg","type":"card"},{"identifier":"ismehimeh.jpeg","type":"icon"}],"abstract":[{"text":"iOS engineer @ EPAM • SwiftUI & UIKit • Passionate about testing and maintainable code • Software Engineering BSc ’18","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/ismehimeh","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/ismehimeh","type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","title":"Sergei Vasilenko (1 note)"},"WWDC20-Icon.png":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC20-Icon.png","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Contributions are welcome!","type":"text"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","title":"Contributions are welcome!","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10057-Identify-trends-with-the-Power-and-Performance-API":{"role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10057-Identify-trends-with-the-Power-and-Performance-API","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10057-identify-trends-with-the-power-and-performance-api","type":"topic","title":"Identify trends with the Power and Performance API","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Track your app’s performance metrics in custom team dashboards, bug reporting systems, and other custom workflows with the Power and Performance Metrics and Diagnostics API. Explore how you can access the same data that drives the Power and Performance analysis tools in Xcode to quickly identify trends and regressions. Learn how to leverage diagnostic signatures and logs — including call stack trees — to prioritize and debug issues. And discover how you can integrate this API with your development team’s existing tools to troubleshoot issues quickly, offering better overall performance for people who use your app."}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC21-10258-Understand-and-eliminate-hangs-from-your-app":{"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc21-10258-understand-and-eliminate-hangs-from-your-app","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Discover how you can track down hangs and delays in your app. We’ll show you tools and methods to discover hangs and their causes, learn about anti-patterns that can lead to hangs, explore best practices for eliminating hangs like GCD, and provide guidance on when you should consider asynchronous code to improve your app performance.","type":"text"}],"title":"Understand and eliminate hangs from your app","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10258-Understand-and-eliminate-hangs-from-your-app"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10077-Eliminate-animation-hitches-with-XCTest":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10077-Eliminate-animation-hitches-with-XCTest","abstract":[{"text":"Animations can dramatically enhance the user experience of your app, provide a sense of direct manipulation, and help people to better understand the results of their actions. Animation hitches can break that experience. Discover how to use XCTest to detect interruptions to smooth scrolling and animations, and learn how to catch regressions before they affect the people relying on your app.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10077-eliminate-animation-hitches-with-xctest","kind":"article","title":"Eliminate animation hitches with XCTest","role":"sampleCode"},"WWDC20-10081-hang-example.jpeg":{"identifier":"WWDC20-10081-hang-example.jpeg","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10081-hang-example.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"WWDC20-10081-launch-time-example.jpeg":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC20-10081-launch-time-example.jpeg","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10081-launch-time-example.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"ismehimeh.jpeg":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/ismehimeh.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"ismehimeh.jpeg","alt":null,"type":"image"},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2020/10081":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2020\/10081","checksum":null,"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2020\/10081","type":"download"},"WWDC20-10081-metrics-payloads.jpeg":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC20-10081-metrics-payloads.jpeg","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10081-metrics-payloads.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC21-10087-Diagnose-Power-and-Performance-regressions-in-your-app":{"role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc21-10087-diagnose-power-and-performance-regressions-in-your-app","type":"topic","title":"Diagnose Power and Performance regressions in your app","abstract":[{"text":"Quickly discover how to identify priorities when viewing power and performance regressions. Learn how to track metrics that have regressed with device-and percentile-specific information, so you can focus your efforts on optimization and save valuable development time. We’ll also show you how to track down common anti-patterns in your app that wear out device storage, help you customize your workflows, and add App Store Connect APIs to help you stay up to date on your app’s real-world performance.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10087-Diagnose-Power-and-Performance-regressions-in-your-app","kind":"article"},"WWDC20.jpeg":{"identifier":"WWDC20.jpeg","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"https://":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Blog"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/","title":"Blog","url":"https:\/\/","type":"link"},"WWDC20-10081-callstack-example.jpeg":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC20-10081-callstack-example.jpeg","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10081-callstack-example.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC21-10203-Triage-TestFlight-crashes-in-Xcode-Organizer":{"role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc21-10203-triage-testflight-crashes-in-xcode-organizer","type":"topic","title":"Triage TestFlight crashes in Xcode Organizer","abstract":[{"text":"Learn how Xcode Organizer makes it easier and faster to triage and fix crashes. We’ll explore how you can get access to crash information and feedback from your TestFlight testers just moments after they occur. And we’ll show you how to analyze crashes, view metrics, and even share crash information among your team.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10203-Triage-TestFlight-crashes-in-Xcode-Organizer","kind":"article"}}}